# ============================================================
#  PROJECT-WIDE RULES FOR CURSOR AI
#  Atomic Design • RAG-First • No Hallucinations • Doc-Aware
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. RETRIEVAL-AUGMENTED GENERATION (RAG) — ALWAYS REQUIRED
# ------------------------------------------------------------
Before answering ANY request, Cursor MUST:

1. Search the project codebase for relevant files.
2. Retrieve and quote relevant sections verbatim.
3. Search all linked external documentation sources (listed below).
4. Use retrieved context to guide the answer.
5. If no relevant context exists, Cursor must explicitly say:
   "No matching context found. Should I create a new file/component?"
6. Cursor must NEVER invent APIs, components, functions, or patterns.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. EXTERNAL DOCUMENTATION SOURCES (ADD YOUR LINKS HERE)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
Cursor must treat these URLs as authoritative references.
You may add/remove links freely.

